ascents.name: Hand Grenade
ascents.comment: I climb v8 in the gym. It's just..sometimes the gym is outside. And soft.

ascents.name: New Religion
ascents.comment: Two moves. Two VERY GOOD moves. But..two moves nonetheless. Gave a couple good goes on the first session, but that ended with a massive flapper. Came back with a vengeance and M-Flashed!

ascents.name: Subterranean
ascents.comment: Secretly psyched Kenny couldn't do it, so I can tell myself it wasn't soft. Though, if I'm posting this here, I guess it's not a secret. But wait, Kenny doesn't have an 8a...so screw him.

ascents.name: The King
ascents.comment: This climb's got it all. Sick Africa flake feature, jugs, crimps, slopers, pinches, heel hooks, drop knees, mantels, flaggots, toe hooks, double knee bars, bat hangs. THIS is rock climbing. Shout out blue crew for the snaps and spots and waiting for my ass to get up this soft boulder. CATHEDRUHHHH. CHUUUHCH. ISM!

ascents.name: Yuji's Dyno
ascents.comment: I think sand was higher than usual... Same move, but maybe a bit less committing because the boulder is like a foot or two shorter right now? It's too bad there are more good holds halfway up, making the dyno contrived as all hell, but great fun nonetheless. Took about 10 goes and a pinky pad, but worth it!

ascents.name: Vision Quest
ascents.comment: Third GO. I went on a Vision Quest; put my mind, body, and the boy's hole to the test. "Our mini-pads will blot out the sun." "Then we shall climb in the shade."

ascents.name: Boing Dexter
ascents.comment: Sussed the mantle and dropped on the flash go, because Soft Second GO is more points, right?

ascents.name: Spongebob Squarepad Sit
ascents.comment: Felt vsoft. But Ryan and Kenny didn't pull, so I'll take it.

ascents.name: Starfox
ascents.comment: Log-book, No score No score; skipped the first move. Probably v5 from there? Would be amazing if it were a standalone boulder.

ascents.name: That Hi-Pro Glow
ascents.comment: Knew this was my style and I really should've flashed. (Who put that decoy hueco there?!) Still very psyched and probably my trip-favorite.

ascents.name: Super Troopers
ascents.comment:
"DOWNGRADE THE BOULDER" -- "He already downgraded the boulder!...He can't downgrade it further!"

"Do you wanna know why I pulled you over?" -- "Littering and....littering and....littering and...not calling this boulder soft."

Mother of God.

ascents.name: Solo Endeavors Stand
ascents.comment: Full line is unreal sick. The stand is cool, too. Only two moves but TOTAL LIMITTTT.

ascents.name: Near Miss
ascents.comment:
Back prow on boulder near Lost at Sea: One-mover...but damn, that one move is fun (not to mention soooft)!

edit: Near Miss... I think the 'left low grainy sidepull' is gone. Just right smear and pogo dead point to the jug thing is the way now.

ascents.name: So Close
ascents.comment: 3rd go. Hit for the cycle today!

ascents.name: Pepsi Challenge
ascents.comment: Why didn't I listen to myself about trying the crimp beta sooner? And why didn't SHEAMUS, THE UNDERTAKER, CM PUNK, TRIPLE H AND THE BIG SHOW LISTEN TO JOHN CENA'S WARNING TO STAY OUT OF THE RING AT THE WWE SUUUUPER SLAAAAAM!

ascents.name: Tin Man
ascents.comment: Had to wait for Pinchy to muster up the energy to SSG this so I could go for the send train. Choo-choo! Shoutout Aiden and Bill for knowing exactly what we were talking about. Shoutout my left forearm skin, or at least what's left of it.

ascents.name: The Hueco Crimper
ascents.comment: Ja, so dis ist zie sandiest vee got during zie trip. And it vas goot. And that's not a reference to the boulder literally sitting on sand. Turns out all it takes is a couple beers to forget that your injuries exist. Night sessions are tough when everything in Leavenworth stops serving food at 9. But shoutout The Loft. Despite its 3.5 star rating on Yelp, this place is an area testpiece. Free Galaga and I would've been able to pull a soft one-of-anything on Davey...but the alternative medicine guy was lecturing us while sitting in the Player 1 seat. Hey, at least we learned that all plant roots grow counter-clockwise.

ascents.name: Cujo
ascents.comment: You really just gotta grab this boulder by the haunches and....hump it into submission!

ascents.name: Blonde Ambition
ascents.comment: I thought it was easier than the shorter version. I guess nobody else did..

ascents.name: Erotic Terrorist
ascents.comment: Obviously would be much more swedge without the chimney dab boulder. Shout out Shirley and Scott for chilling in the Ice Caves on Night 1 until No-yes and I worked out soft send-trainable beta.

ascents.name: Bridalveil Pogo
ascents.comment: Night sesh send! Not sure if soft or just my style. Although, soft is my style, so--I guess...both? JBS training gave me the wrist confidence to pull up into the underjug. Pogo-less lunge to the bucket is rad. Milly crew went hard on this successful day trip to the Valley!

ascents.name: Kauk Problem Sit
ascents.comment: I can finally be in the crew that bitches about having nothing left to do at the Knobs when someone suggests we go to the Knobs. Yay..

ascents.name: G23 Arete
ascents.comment: I haven't made up my mind about this climb. On the one hand, I split a tip...

ascents.name: Black Matter
ascents.comment: This thing is softer than Dion Lewis' ACL. And if you disagree, well, now you're just Lion Dewis. Nice movement and ergonomic holds, but sharp and pretty lowball.

ascents.name: WoodYard arete
ascents.comment: Didn't think I could punt any harder than I did last time I was here. But sure enough, I managed to take an even bigger fall from the very top. Luckily, I pulled some hard justice in the fanny from Fanny to avoid the exposed rock in the landing zone. But after a classic crush, suss and brush combo from Fanny's Dingus, I ran up this amazing climb. Atlantis better watch out.. new favorite boulder in the Valley!

ascents.name: Atlantis
ascents.comment: Log-book, No score Repeat. This is the only thing in the valley I can climb. Good thing it's one of my all-time favs.

ascents.name: Atlantis
ascents.comment: Log-book, No score Give me a break...just psyched on this thing. First go repeat.

ascents.name: Ian's Prow
ascents.comment: Fingies went stupid numb on flash go..which is why I didn't feel that big ol' flapper on the power bump. Went second GO from the start after warming up on the topout suss. But I digress...Awesome movement, perfect crimps and fun topout.

ascents.name: Atlantis
ascents.comment: Definitely lives up to the hype. So psyched on this thing. From the setting and scenery to the movement and features, this bloc has it all. High up on my list of favorite ascents to date. The headlamp night sesh just added to the epicness.

ascents.name: Silent Spotter
ascents.comment: This line is borderline perfect. Everything is ergonomic and directional as hell. The tallus landing kind of takes away from its aesthetic-ness, but holy crap it climbs so well.

ascents.name: Medusa
ascents.comment: This, ladies and gents, is SlimB's style. Funky heel hook and a bit technical. Cool holds all around and super interesting movement/beta. Into this!

ascents.name: Tooth Fairy
ascents.comment: Twinning and winning all day with my boy Dylan...until he pulled a P. Unter on this thing. But Shirley and I still crushed. Shoulda went last time, but Davey's topout beta adds a grade...a grade I like to call, Violence Road.

ascents.name: Greasefire
ascents.comment: Fitness day, party day! Stoked this went. Classic not using Davey-beta. This roof testpiece has it all...knee bars, heel hooks, JBS..the works. What do you call that Earthbound character after he gets strong?

ascents.name: Year of the Cockroach
ascents.comment: Second go after sussing. This thing is so much fun. All that training on #52 at the Sandbox is paying off! I'll give it a full value soft 6 because that fat left-hand meat-hook jug for the topout is completely missing now making for a pumped techy mantle.

ascents.name: Power Windows
ascents.comment: Scooter Limb is about to have the best bouldering day of his life. First half of the climb is three stars! Unfortunately, the topout is a joke. Pinchy would've static'ed the crux.

ascents.name: Red Spark
ascents.comment: Wow, that deadpoint felt so much easier than last time. Stoked my finger is feeling better!...for now.

ascents.name: Jean Claude Van Damme (JCVD)
ascents.comment: So rad. Blew the top twice in a row just so I could do it a third time. Toe hook post-pogo for full value. Last go, best go. Lots of blood shed to send this bloccc.

ascents.name: Shortness of Breath
ascents.comment: Sure, it's contrived, but great movement. Tsee-yahh!

ascents.name: The Persistence of Time
ascents.comment: Might be soft for taller people, but it took me three sessions of work to get it. So I'll take the 6!

ascents.name: Father's Day
ascents.comment: Don't know why Benny and Kenjamin were messing around with heels, toe hooks, thumbderclings for like 45 minutes. "Looks like you just go straight up"...commence send train.

ascents.name: Bear Hug
ascents.comment: Was trying to avoid using a left heel. But I just had to suck it up for one go, and it was incredibly soft.

ascents.name: The White Arete
ascents.comment: NIce to do something that shut me down last year. But not nice that it had to be this shart pile.  Eh, it's ok.

ascents.name: Footless traverse
ascents.comment: Log-book, No score Never actually got the chance to try from the start. But I imagine the 3 crimp moves I skipped don't add much to the boulder. Just wanted to get to the Bezoss hold asap.

ascents.name: Walrus in a Blender
ascents.comment: Check out that boss hold! It's like the The Hulk of Hueco. Way easier than Bloody Flapper...or maybe I just got lucky.

ascents.name: V-Obsession
ascents.comment: Paul's beta is actually pretty freaking cool. Hand-heel matches are fairly classic...but heel-hand matches are NEXT LEVEL. Just a bit annoying with the adjacent rock in the way.

ascents.name: Schadenfraud
ascents.comment: Had a nice gym session in the Martini Cave to escape the rain. Scott was vPsyched in here. This one took me quite a bit of work to figure out my beta before I could do it. Nails AF! Don't worry Scott, tomorrow you'll be right as rain...

ascents.name: *Hobbit in a Blender
ascents.comment:
First go, second day. Damn, this line is so cool.

PS: Has anything in Hueco NOT broken?

ascents.name: Dragonfly
ascents.comment: First go, second day. Decently interesting upward trending traverse from finger crack to jug rail...but THAT'S where the fun really begins. Shoutout Paul for Full Service! I'd like to think it was my send of D-Fly that really inspired him to try hard.

ascents.name: Lobster Claw
ascents.comment: I'm a simple man. I throw a kneebar, I give 3 stars.

ascents.name: Dude where's my pipe
ascents.comment: This place is great, but why the hell does it have to be so sharp? That pocket is UNcomfortable, and dangerous! This minestrone is extra hot. I know it's under a dollar, Janet, but I'm having trouble digesting properly. I hate your mom!

ascents.name: Have a Seat
ascents.comment: Really nice trailside arete. Fun moves. Top was a little more strenuous than expected, but soft nonetheless.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Feature request to Jens: When the word "kneebar" is used in the Comment field, autopopulate Stars field to ***.

ascents.name: Sugar Babies Stand
ascents.comment: Skipped those god-awful stacked edges by bumping straight to the jug. It wasn't pretty...I made this thing look worse than JOHN CENA IS GOING TO MAKE THE UNDERTAKER'S FACE LOOK BY THE END OF THE  BATTLE ROYALE AT WWE SUUUUPER SLAAAAM THIS SUNDAY NIGHT!

ascents.name: The Flake
ascents.comment: Can't tell if my style or just really soft. Definitely both. Giant toe-hook, a couple slaps and an easy mantle.

ascents.name: The Undercling
ascents.comment: Pinch the undercling with the right and then BEEEEE-UUPPP! Shoutout Good Mood Food. Breakfast croissant and a drip coffee every morning. Ol' reliable.

ascents.name: Purple sticky punch
ascents.comment: Didn't love the first few moves from the sit, but the features made up for it. Shout-out Kenny's post-last burn dyno beta send. Also shout-out Pike for moving the death rock out of the landing zone...I knew we brought you along for some reason.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: 10 foot boulder just up the hill from the ranger station. Climbs up the left arete on a right seam and left crimps. This climb needs a name. The holds are really cool and the movement is superb. Just lovely, through and through.

ascents.name: Delirium
ascents.comment: Starting the day on a soft v5! This climb is okey-dokey.

ascents.name: Aztec
ascents.comment: After falling on that last throw 4 times, I was already spotting my landing when I stuck it on the last go. Really fun boulder!

ascents.name: Smile For The Green Dragon
ascents.comment: Piqued my interest when Mike told me the name. Interest dwindled when we got to the 6 foot boulder. Didn't backstep the first move in an attempt to make it less soft. Soft.

ascents.name: Atlas
ascents.comment: Big ol' move! Lots of different ways to do this. I opted for the high right heel, much to the chagrin of my hammy...and my wrist apparently.

ascents.name: Lobster claw
ascents.comment: So I was takin' a walk the other day and I seen a boulderer. He seemed to be a bit frustrated, as if he had forgotten his beta and havin' a hard time findin' it. So after watchin' him struggle for a while, I decide to go over and lend a helping hand, you know? "Hello, can I be of any assistance? It seems to me that you've lost something. I would like to help you find it." He replied: "Oh yes, you have lost something. You've lost...your flash."

ascents.name: Trogdor
ascents.comment: DAMN.

ascents.name: Anti Hero
ascents.comment: (MHMSSG) Finally I wasn't the last to send. In fact, I was the first! And good thing because it's probably less soft now that Shirley ripped off the jug. JBS will not have me, tsee-yah! Someone said to start this matched on the arete 6 inches off the ground? No thx, bro. I start where andyliu84 starts. And that's more meaningful I think.

ascents.name: And The Livin's Easy
ascents.comment: First couple trav moves are meh. Then a sweet cross off that crimp to the pinch jug. Blew flash because of dumb topout to the right beta.

ascents.name: Heavy Artillery (High Start)
ascents.comment: The baseball sized bruise on my ass can attest that I did not flash this. Cover up that rock! Wish we had more time at this boulder for PBR and Soft Grenade.

ascents.name: Kauk Problem
ascents.comment: I need to get better on small holds. Glad to have done this. Had to try real hard to stick the second crimp.

ascents.name: Flying Birdie
ascents.comment: Left hand start hold and foot were pretty disgustingly wet and mossy. But rad feature and moved quite well with a big move to a jug. Super fun. If only it weren't in Tahoe.

ascents.name: Cocaine corner
ascents.comment: Felt impossible until the futuristic 'hand-flag' technique was discovered. Then it was soft. Got inspired after witnessing the fitness of Fanny getting his fanny up King Air. Night climbing > dinner.

ascents.name: Europa
ascents.comment: Kinda sick movement along the lip. Very nice mantel, though!

ascents.name: Ticket to Venus
ascents.comment: Now introducing #2 on the list entitled "Climbs I've Completed In Less Burns Than David". Questy topout (trav left..weak). V5 is the easiest grade in the Jupes.

ascents.name: Hit Man
ascents.comment: Went easily after I found the right foot. Neat pinch and cool move to jug. Peel over is a bit wonky.

ascents.name: Ladder Detail
ascents.comment: mFlash. Left undercling beta makes this thing cake. Davey one-two makes this thing messed.

ascents.name: Jedi Jake Stand
ascents.comment: Felt really hard until I used an actual foothold. Really cool moves on beautiful and ergonomic features. Shout out...dat hand pinch. Would love to be able to do the sit. Maybe next year. Shirley was a man amongst men on this boulder.

ascents.name: Beached Whale
ascents.comment: Surprisingly good and interesting moves early on, traversing into some awesome sloper jugs. Might consider 3 stars if it wasn't directly next to other area classics like Silent Spotter...and Munchkin Lunch. As far as the mantel goes, they certainly got the name right. Also, not signing CRush and Hommer's score cards.

ascents.name: Space Monkey
ascents.comment: Check my style out!

ascents.name: Johnson's Arete
ascents.comment: Fun climb, cool holds and good movement. If only it weren't Stoney sandstone, this thing would be illll. Top was pretty scary.

ascents.name: The Wave
ascents.comment: Dyno was super fun! Psych was so low, but this thing got us highhhh..and led to a productive evening.

ascents.name: The Swedge
ascents.comment: Mflash. The Swedge? Yeah, that thing is okay...Okay? Okay?? I mean, the boulder's all-time!! Shirley's beta was too subtle, so instead, I drove a PASSAT!!! all the way to the top. Shout out...Dylan.

ascents.name: Obe Problem Right
ascents.comment: I consider this the best 5/6..and not the other way around. Scooter found some really sick beta for this one. 10/26/15 Edit: DGing for the pyramid.

ascents.name: Go Granny Go Right
ascents.comment: I think I liked it more than the original. Cool heel hook --> toe hook switch into the big swing. Then compression up the arete was very fun. Toe hook was so bomber my foot got stuck on first go.

ascents.name: Done with the south
ascents.comment: Probably my hardest flash. Stoked on this  beautifully pure line. Great movement, fun holds, airy mantel. How is this not 3 stars? Definitely one of my favorite climbs ever. Didn't dab = stronger than Mr. Hoss?

ascents.name: Mr. Happy
ascents.comment: Mr. Happy made my fingers Mr. Sads. The pockets are so non-ergonomic, but it was actually really fun figuring out how to use them. Needless to say my beta was wayyy better than Davey's.

ascents.name: Dyno Time
ascents.comment: Cool big move. That jug is sickk.

ascents.name: Cobra Kahn
ascents.comment: Long uphill hike. Wouldn't have found it without a little help from a certain special Fanny. Possibly the most stunning feature I've seen. Movement was great too, once I unlocked the subtleties of the big first move.

ascents.name: Stumblebum Traverse
ascents.comment: Holy soft. But great holds, cool movement, tons of fun. Not as aesthetic as Fart Fig, doe.

ascents.name: Gatorade
ascents.comment: Cool balancey face climb. Was destroying me until I found a subtle foot sequence that worked for me. Akachill send was epic.

ascents.name: Kill by numbers
ascents.comment: Really cool roof. I was being killed by the number of betas being used on it, but once I found my own, not too bad. Second try after sussing.

ascents.name: Kelly's arete
ascents.comment: Much better than I thought it was gonna be. Blew my flash because Shirley Girth knows a thing or two about ridiculous high stepping. Campusing my foot up for the mantel was sketch, but you know what they say...

ascents.name: Hammerhead
ascents.comment: Holy king line. Surprised myself with this one. But Shirley Girth knows a thing or two about inspiring sends. Crazy cool features, movement, committing dead point up top. Shout out sea of pads and Fanny for spotting. What the spicy!

ascents.name: Jack's Baby
ascents.comment: This took a nice long session ending in the dark. Good times here.

ascents.name: Swank Stretch
ascents.comment: Better than I thought it was gonna be. Turned out to be super fun!

ascents.name: Envy
ascents.comment: Super tricky, weirdly technical sequence. Shout-out Faniel's Dong for sussing, brushing, and crushing.

ascents.name: Pancake House
ascents.comment: 7A? C'mon guys...

ascents.name: Crouching tiger hidden dragon
ascents.comment: Repeat from April 2013. Went through the same process of feeling impossible on burn 1 and then slowly figuring out micro until it goes on burn 20! Still way soft for 7A+. Still a classic.

ascents.name: The Cube
ascents.comment: First tried this thing over two years ago. Glad to finally catch it with some non-unbearable temps!

ascents.name: Beareagle
ascents.comment: I did Bear over a year and a half ago...so I guess not a legit flash, but I'ma do me. The fact that this thing felt so easy after hiking through shin-high snow for an hour makes me wonder about its grade. Having said that, really good climb!

ascents.name: Serengeti
ascents.comment: Right variation. Very cool big cross and toe hook. Much easier than Serengeti Direct. Only one hard move.

ascents.name: Perfectly Chicken
ascents.comment: Probably the cleanest, most aesthetic and flowy line in Buttermilk Country. Where's the option for 4 stars?

ascents.name: Serengeti
ascents.comment: Last go, best go. Sooooup!

ascents.name: Sucker Punch
ascents.comment: Lil' Dicky we made it! Shout out Jay Phister.

ascents.name: Rene
ascents.comment: Proud. Felt like one of the hardest things I've done. Stoked! Also popped a darn pulley on the send go. WTF.

ascents.name: Go Granny Go
ascents.comment: Finally.

ascents.name: Fly Boy Arete
ascents.comment: Yep, for sure feels 2 grades harder than Birthday Direct...oh wait.

ascents.name: Magic Beans
ascents.comment: Breakage? Not v7. Thought it was real fun, though.

ascents.name: Timeless
ascents.comment: I thought it was soft, until I heard it took David 12 goes...I'm surprised it took HIM so many tries. Great climb. Timeless classic.

ascents.name: Green Hornet
ascents.comment: One of my all time favorites. So stoked to finally get it.

ascents.name: Crouching tiger hidden dragon
ascents.comment: It may be soft, but it made me hard! One of my favorites.

ascents.name: Son Of Claudius Rufus
ascents.comment: Pumpy and fun. Great mantle. First V5 onsight!

ascents.name: Chizam
ascents.comment: Fun lunge.

ascents.name: Watch the Dog
ascents.comment: My longest standing project. Stoked!

ascents.name: Lonesome Pine
ascents.comment: Sweet movement on great slopers. Gotta get the sit now.

ascents.name: The Fang (sit)
ascents.comment: So much better than the stand. Awesome move out to the fang.

ascents.name: Organ Grinder
ascents.comment: I enjoyed it.

ascents.name: The Ramp
ascents.comment: I am very fucking surprised Sunshine didn’t go 10 burns ago

ascents.name: Central Scrutinizer
ascents.comment: Is this the thing between Little Wing and Smiley Face? Started on two chest high slimy jugs. Up left to a really good hold, right hand heel match, bump up to those bulges above the lip, go a bit right to the gastoning sloper rail and top on with that swag kneebar. Actually super good movement.

ascents.name: Boulder Geek
ascents.comment: Improbable first move for my weak, hurt fingies. But Ben's (subtle) backstep pogo somehow felt ok.

ascents.name: Slippery Arete
ascents.comment: Looks and climbs quite nice. At least as good as Father's Day. Beautiful Breasts is right down the hill, but the erect nipple on this one makes it an areola testpiece!

ascents.name: Swordfish
ascents.comment: Dingus!

ascents.name: Tombstone
ascents.comment:
I would not say this climb is worth the hike. However, seeing Ryan rip his pants off after falling off this climb was definitely worth the hike.

"Watch out!"

ascents.name: Tampax Arete
ascents.comment: Easily the coolest boulder I did this trip. Yeahhh...I didn't do much.

ascents.name: Moonshine Roof
ascents.comment: Aw shiiiit, I see you, Hueco! I see you!

ascents.name: Warm Up Roof
ascents.comment: Warm Up Roof? More like Get Flash Pumped And Don't Send Anything Else The Rest Of The Day Roof. I ain't even mad though..that jump move is sick as.

ascents.name: Girls of juarez
ascents.comment: Hueco, you crazy for this one! Super funky...I mean, the first move is from one boulder to another. Oh and that kneebar??...that kneebar.

ascents.name: T-Bone Shuffle
ascents.comment: Last night I had a bad dream. I was trapped inside Hueco, then I asked "Is that really such a bad thing?" They keepin' people out the park daily, keep on blamin' people that ain't never had reservations. Guess not. Last night I pulled up on the jug at the top like, uh, nice choss, rip it!

ascents.name: Too Many Words
ascents.comment: You see, a boulder like me -- A FREAK -- A boulder..like..listen, I know why you choose to have your little.."bouldering" sessions in broad daylight. I know why you'd be afraid to climb this at night. Because it has a pretty airy topout with a questionable landing.

ascents.name: Oh My
ascents.comment: Short, but OK. Always nice when a climb feels way easier than the last time you were on it.

ascents.name: So Sweet
ascents.comment: Jugs up until, just--well...you see where I'm going with this. Tree dab on first go, but fun enough to do it twice!

ascents.name: Lost At Sea
ascents.comment: Honestly pretty hard, but HSG isn't a thing. Holds of every variety on this bad boy and even a Squamish shuffle. It's finally burger time, Kian.

ascents.name: Butterfly
ascents.comment: From one move in. The legit start is heinous. Was not gonna go in Humiderabad without chalk and big shoes. The rest was real good, though. Gaston, high foot, come into the undercling jug, slap to lip and nobody knows what I'm talking about so I'll stop. But you can imagine!

ascents.name: The Snarl
ascents.comment: Not particularly soft, but obligatory given the Second GO. The move to the lip is a little confusing. You just gotta put your foot in your own ass WHICH IS WHERE JOHN CENA'S FOOT IS GONNA BE AS HE DEFENDS HIS BELT THIS SUNDAY NIGHT AT THE WWE SUUUUPER SLAAAAM.

ascents.name: Claim Jumper
ascents.comment: Holy cow, that pinch you jump to is so awesome. May be the most fun I've had on a boulder this trip. Plus, this baby lands itself on the coveted 'Took Less Burns Than David' list.

ascents.name: The Pocket
ascents.comment: Really, really good. Felt like the White Flight of Leavenworth...but with way bigger holds. Shoutout Blewitt Brewing. With beer and pizza that good, we'll still pay even if you stop serving at 9.

ascents.name: The Icehouse
ascents.comment: Really awesome diamond-shaped pinch/gaston/flip-it! feature. Had tons of fun figuring out my bottom sequence. Left hand was slipping on the arete at the top. Thought I was gonna fall, but blindly found a literal thank-god jug in the dark. Everybody gets one. Tell 'em Peter.

ascents.name: Fridge center
ascents.comment: Really, really good. Found sweet on-the-fly double-gaston beta to get the high foot before moving up to the boss hold. Still, I think the first half of Fridge Right is even cooler. Too bad the top doesn't go. Shoutout SOUTH's Tequila Tuesday.

ascents.name: Twisted Tree
ascents.comment: Oh yeah, I got Twisted Tree months ago...It's nestled safely under the tree.

ascents.name: The Little V4
ascents.comment: What an improbable sequence!

ascents.name: Rated X
ascents.comment: Scared my spotters at the top, but guys, I was good. Guys? GUYS?!

ascents.name: Beaver Cleaver
ascents.comment: Warmed up on the stand. Sure wish it was a little bit longer, but that can be said about most things. Really enjoyed the movement all the way through. Is there anything better than starting the day off with a soft v4? (Hint: see Delirium)

ascents.name: The Nose Left
ascents.comment: Backlog.

ascents.name: Rubik's Cube
ascents.comment: Unnamed left arete on the Rubik's Revenge boulder. Sweet recyclable cube pinch in the middle. Neat sequence and fun topout. Surprised I've never been here before.

ascents.name: Bates Arete
ascents.comment: Thank you based Jqee's right knee smear beta. Lit.

ascents.name: Jedi Mind Tricks
ascents.comment: Was having so much trouble with the opening sequences that were going around, so...classic me, had to go outside the box and just do me. Once I got up into the big gaston I pretty much browned out and cruised. So awesome up there. Psyched to caboose the Sandbox send-train on this off-style testpeice.

ascents.name: Whiskey, beer, and spliff hits for breakfast
ascents.comment: Super cool looking boulder. The movement was really good, too. But there's something about you, Mrs. Sullivan. Oh right, that mono. Don't know if I've ever yarred on one finger like that before. Sandbox?...More like the Sendbox.

ascents.name: Iron Man Traverse
ascents.comment: Only punted last night so I could pull the mFlash/brownpoint today. The rest day continues!

ascents.name: Ahwahnee Arete
ascents.comment: It's like two boulder problems in one! Good to be back in the Valley where I can still get amped on sending v4. Especially nice to mFlash this after charfing last season.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Good holds and cool moves to a balancy topout. Scott said the start jug was creaking when I pulled on. Might just be my fatass, but beware!

ascents.name: Summer Vacation
ascents.comment: One is 3. Three is 5. Five is 4. And four is the magic number. Oh, and twentyone is 9.

ascents.name: Spaceballs
ascents.comment: They've gone to plaid.

ascents.name: The arete
ascents.comment: mFlash. Pretty swag. Cool features and movement. Topping out on the jutting out shelf was odd, exciting and good fun!

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Start at Detached. Trav left and up the arete. LT2S. Nice starting jug block. Arete is cool.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: The process of this one was cool. Felt just so unbalanced and undoable for the first couple burns. Then found one chossy little crimp for opposition. Then it was soft. First move was still annoying, though.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Maybe Medlicott Boulder 1 or something? There's a 6c dyno that goes straight up, but this 4 climbed nicely. So many unnamed climbs this weekend. Kinda lame. But voluuuume is swag.

ascents.name: Snake Eyes Sit
ascents.comment: Harder than Double Dyno., albeit still soft. Those snake eye knobs are pretty cool. Like peacork. Right, Janet?

ascents.name: Double Dyno Sit
ascents.comment: I remember exactly what we did on the boulder. We just looked, OUT! 'Cross the meadows on that little spot on the hilltop. Oh, it was so pretty way up there. We talked about how the lights on the mountains and cars seemed like reflections of the stars. That shone out so pretty and bright, that niiiight.

ascents.name: Bear Hug Arete
ascents.comment: Pretty fun. Nice rock. Good height. Decent movement. But it's in Tahoe. One star.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Not in the book we had, but just up the hill/on the way from/to Tick Tock. Short but a couple of fun compression moves.

ascents.name: Ament Arete
ascents.comment: Sit felt a little awkard, but pretty cool. Couldnt muster for the link up, but the stand was good, too. Crossing out to the crimp beta was fun, but also psyched on Shirley's mantel beta.

ascents.name: Solar Flare
ascents.comment: Probably soft. Cool moves on fat crimps. Mantel is the crux.

ascents.name: Short Train
ascents.comment: I mean, worth doing if you're in the area and want to stay warm without jabbing a knife through your hand. Also, probably as hard as Bachar Cracker.

ascents.name: Slopers and Dopers
ascents.comment: Nice slopers and ginormous feet, but way too short.

ascents.name: Bear Hug Mantle
ascents.comment: Felt harder than I wanted it to. What a feature, though! A little lowball, but that jug is amazing and the mantel is great. Good fun!

ascents.name: Illuminatrix
ascents.comment: Cool holds, great movement and fall-off-the-mountain potential? Sign me up. As if that enormous hueco at the lip wasn't enough, there is also a massive xeno a foot above that. So awesome.

ascents.name: Bicycles and Tricycles
ascents.comment: One hard foot move and one hard lockoff on a razor crimp. After that, super sick movement directly up a pretty tall face. This thing clearly doesn't get enough love. That is...until Shirley, Crush and I ran train on her. I'm losing it!....sploosh.

ascents.name: March Arete
ascents.comment: Repeat. Wow, this thing felt so much easier than last time. This thing is sick with good beta. Fitness train keeps a rollin'.

ascents.name: Standing on the Head of the Dragon
ascents.comment: Repeated this bad boy just so I could document Scooter Limb's worst bouldering day ever. Rolled ankle on first boulder and everything went downhill from there...so to speak. Good run of injury-freeness..but this is pretty classic me. See ya in a month!

ascents.name: Black Cauldron
ascents.comment: Night climbing is fun when stoke is still high! And Davey's first go best go Soul Cali send gave us just enough time to run train on this on the way out and still grab that last 10:30 tram ride. Sickk.

ascents.name: *Cave Problem
ascents.comment: When did this thing break? Huge starting flake is gone! Big cross to sketchy deep heel cam is the way to go.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Random boulder on the way up to Cobra Kahn. A couple moves on good crimps into a jug rail. Then a committing lockoff from a bad dish to the top. A little bit spicy!

ascents.name: Pimpin jeans
ascents.comment: Neat crimps. Not super inspiring.

ascents.name: Self Service
ascents.comment: Cool moves. Fat heel hooks and big holds.

ascents.name: Go Go Gorilla
ascents.comment: Fun first move. The rest was dumb...all two moves of it.

ascents.name: Tendons Give
ascents.comment: Fun movement. Probably V3. Embarrassingly blew the topout on onsight burn. But on the bright side, I got to do it twice!

ascents.name: Zorro
ascents.comment: Super cool block feature and really fun movement from start to finish. Soft v4.

ascents.name: Cue Ball
ascents.comment: Fun problem! Tried this thing a while ago with heinous David "beta"...much better this time around.

ascents.name: La Bocha De Boogy
ascents.comment: Did the static beta a couple seasons ago. All points off dyno is just so classic  though. Outrageous fun.

ascents.name: Thighmaster
ascents.comment: First go this year. Last year felt impossible. lolwut. These thighs...these thighs have seen a lot of loves but they're never gonna see another one like I had with you.

ascents.name: Atlas
ascents.comment: Very fun movement. That sidepull is an awesome hold.

ascents.name: Superfly
ascents.comment: Man, this thing felt hard. But I guess not as hard as last year! Backflag toe hook is very cool.

ascents.name: Ceramic Salamander
ascents.comment: Pretty soft. A bit of a scare factor with the questionable landing. Climbs great!

ascents.name: Standing on the Head of the Dragon
ascents.comment: Quite a unique feature. Cool climb. Shit, it's hard though.

ascents.name: Sunshine Daydream
ascents.comment: Freaking pumpy and proud boulder. Direct line still has to go. Using just holds on the face has much better movement.

ascents.name: Dope Man Short
ascents.comment: Send train!

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Sharp crimps through the center face of Middle Boulder.

ascents.name: The Seam
ascents.comment: Cool line. Felt easier than it did a year and a half ago.

ascents.name: *Bowling Pin
ascents.comment: Using Scott's impromptu beta. Sick climb.

ascents.name: Easy in an Easy Chair
ascents.comment: Last day of the trip; megaproj goes down. Stoked, but pissed off at this choss-pile.

ascents.name: Shots Fired
ascents.comment: Classic UCLA rock wall v3. Top 100 v4 in 3 goes? Must be soft.

ascents.name: Tai Fighter
ascents.comment: Very cool looking rock, but the first couple moves felt so stupidly awkward. Heel hook cross over a gaston? Dumb.

ascents.name: Palminator
ascents.comment: Worlds easier than Easy Chair. What the eff.

ascents.name: Trad Killer
ascents.comment: People overhyped its softness. Soft for a Top 100 v4, but solid for normal v4...at least at my height.

ascents.name: *Black mark
ascents.comment: Worked it at the end of the day a couple days before. Got it first-go on send day. Sweet climb.

ascents.name: Frank's Problem
ascents.comment: Fun and pumpy with an exciting topout. 10/26/15 Edit: DGing for the pyramid.

ascents.name: Game of Death
ascents.comment: Very fun. A little committing with boulder below topout and slanted ground below first half. Sweet moves!

ascents.name: Snake Eyes
ascents.comment: Blew the topout on the onsight...but learned to love it.

ascents.name: The Spirit of the Forest
ascents.comment: Cool name, cool moves.

ascents.name: Paradise Blend
ascents.comment: Cool climb. Hard until we figured out the beta...then soft.

ascents.name: Unknown
ascents.comment: Right side of Reed's Arete. Soft for Black, but fun.

ascents.name: Square Dance
ascents.comment: Little confused where this one starts. Hard if started matched under roof, soft if left hand starts outside.

ascents.name: Impulse Control
ascents.comment: Forced line. But fun-ish.

ascents.name: Beer Tumor right
ascents.comment: I loved this line. Great movement. And first V4 flash!

ascents.name: Bleached Bones
ascents.comment: Cool looking line. First move was annoyingly reachy for me.

ascents.name: Solarium
ascents.comment: Sharp pockets with a good hard move at the end.

ascents.name: Mothership Connection
ascents.comment: Finally.

ascents.name: The Fang
ascents.comment: Contrived as all hell.

ascents.name: Not So Thin Lizzy
ascents.comment: Decent movement. Subtle.

ascents.name: Dead Bug
ascents.comment: Took a handful of goes. But it probably shouldn't have. Fun low ball though!

ascents.name: B1 Traverse
ascents.comment: So pumped by the end.

ascents.name: Ketron Classic
ascents.comment: Lots of fun.

ascents.name: Weekender
ascents.comment: Long, pumpy, good movement.

ascents.name: Eagle
ascents.comment: Sick line. Fun moves.

ascents.name: Swiss Cheese
ascents.comment: Decent moves. VERY soft for the grade.

ascents.name: Burn Off
ascents.comment: I liked this a lot.

ascents.name: La Bocha de boogie
ascents.comment: Static beta ftw. Prob not v4 though.

ascents.name: Obe Problem Direct
ascents.comment: Cool looking rock.

ascents.name: South Street
ascents.comment: Cool, but short.

ascents.name: Paul Rocks
ascents.comment: Decently fun. Not very proud, though.

ascents.name: March Arete
ascents.comment: I liked it. Blind throw around the arete is exciting.

ascents.name: Pancake
ascents.comment: Really fun short line with an exciting top out.

ascents.name: Fly if You're a Midget
ascents.comment: Always good to squeeze in some anti-style every once in a while. Must be soft though cuz I don't climb v3 slab.

ascents.name: Pocket Rocket
ascents.comment: First pull's not the easiest thing in the world. But vnice moves.

ascents.name: Briefs
ascents.comment: Had fun working out this anti-style problem by myself. A bit wet, which made it all the more exciting.

ascents.name: The Tentacles
ascents.comment: wth guys...this is definitely called The Octopus. I don't care how many beers I drank, I think I'd remember if there was actually another Spongebob reference on this boulder.

ascents.name: Cellar Door
ascents.comment: Not 100% we did it right. Start on the Fridge Right start jug, move into the gaston, bump big to the shelf, mantel up from the there. Pretty sweet!

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Small overhang just before Abstraction. Had to occupy myself while the strong bois were on Kobra Kon.

ascents.name: El Burro
ascents.comment: Man, I wish there was an option for Hard Second GO, because this thing actually isn't soft. But such is 8a. Big-ish movies and the top is pretty tricky. Classic.

ascents.name: Choss Training
ascents.comment: Did this while waiting for the big boys at Diaphanous. Seemed silly at the time, but the slo-mo video is actually pretty satisfying. Top is superchoss.

ascents.name: Sign of the Cross
ascents.comment: Nice looking line. But so sharp and feet and the beginning are lacking. Sounds like a personal problem...

ascents.name: Tree Crack
ascents.comment: Where did we land on burgers?

ascents.name: Killer
ascents.comment: Amazing face climb. The rock is actually insanely good here...Orange, crystally, super sharp granite..kind of like a JTree type. Or the Milks if they were left in the sun for too long.

ascents.name: Gold Wall
ascents.comment: Columbia may be a bit slimy, covered in poison oak and not soft...but the features...the features will keep me coming back!!

ascents.name: The Sword
ascents.comment: A couple surprisingly powerful moves gets you to the start of the juggy flake system at about 12 feet. 8 feet of glory lie-backing gets you to the long, high foot reach to the apex. Boy, that really adds up.

ascents.name: Drugstore Cowboy
ascents.comment: Actually really fun. Fatty lock-bar for the topout. Also, Pinchy is dead. Also also Pinchy is dead.

ascents.name: The Lamb
ascents.comment: What a hilarious misunderstanding.

ascents.name: Pretty Girl
ascents.comment: Don't like her?! What's wrong with her? She's rich. She's beautiful. She's got a huge...fin-like dihedral feature! So rad. First go after figuring out me betas...which took about 12. Shoutout Bavarian Bistro & Bar. Meant to go to Stein, but walked through the wrong door. May have been a blessing in disguise because the schnitzels were out of this country.

ascents.name: Max Attacks
ascents.comment: Lowball, sure. But two really good moves and a fun mantle.

ascents.name: Squeezer
ascents.comment: I know, I know..I barely know her. BUT, very fun pogo over the spiny's.

ascents.name: Grim Reality
ascents.comment: So so cool. Not as scary as it looks. Especially after watching Andrew's comp-style backwards stemming send. Yep, yep, yep, yep, yep, yep...indeeeed!

ascents.name: Distilled Iron Left
ascents.comment: 3-dimensional climbing on this one working through those slots in the cutout. Nice movement low.

ascents.name: The Nose Right
ascents.comment: Backlog.

ascents.name: Triple cracks arete
ascents.comment: If I flail on Triple Cracks and do an easier line instead I'ma make it look sexy.

ascents.name: Beak Traverse
ascents.comment: Soft 3rd go. Good to get back outside...even if it was just wrasslin' Kauk.

ascents.name: Birthday Direct
ascents.comment: My god, this was the first boulder I'd ever tried in Bishop with a Lu Wu and Greg Hart type like 4 years ago. It's still really hard. Until you realize the pinch is a jug. Then it becomes soft.

ascents.name: The Scoop
ascents.comment: Pretty psyched. Not so much on the send, but more on the fact that I was able to find a boulder that isn't soft. Redline send!

ascents.name: Golden Rastafarian
ascents.comment: Worth going out to Kitty for. So nice, we did it twice! First move double clutch is def the way to goooo...

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: This was on that one boulder just down the hill from that other boulder. Start low left. Trend right up a seam with some nice holds, nice opposing feet, big jug over the lip. Fun, easy mantel. Good fun. Shout out Carly Assandra for her first v3!

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: So much volume. So few names. Up the middle of the Medlicott Warmup Boulder. Couple of hard pulls to a big move from bucket to bucket. Sharp!

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Medlicott Warmup Boulder. Traverse from the left arete into the jug rail. Big move to the top. First couple moves are cool, then gets dabby with the big rock. Then a few more deece moves.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Last one I swear! Also on Medlicott Boulder 1 or something. Started low right, nice cross off a high right heel hook and trended up and left. Tough first pull. Nice movement.

ascents.name: Subway
ascents.comment: Hard and sharp but(t) fun.

ascents.name: The Crystal Arete
ascents.comment: First move was good fun. The rest was a chossy, shelf trav. Worth doing if you're at the Black Matter boulder waiting for Natalie to send.

ascents.name: Double Dyno
ascents.comment: You are the most beautiful line...on the face. On the whole wide face. Oooh. And when you're on a boulder, depending on the boulder, I bet you are definitely in the top threeee..good looking lines on the boulder. And when I saw you at the Knobs I thought.. what is this line..doing...at the Knobs?!  How did the Knobs get a problem like that to a sector like this? Good one, Knobs! You're a legend, Knobs! It's so beautiful. It could be a two star line in the Valley!

ascents.name: Snake Eyes
ascents.comment: It was daytime.

ascents.name: Raw Honey
ascents.comment: Not soft. But soft. For soft's sake.

ascents.name: Mars Attack
ascents.comment: Chossy bung.

ascents.name: Kor Problem
ascents.comment: Woah. More people should do this. Pretty face, nice features, huge....tracts of land! And no singing!! ....we're coming with you..?

ascents.name: Once upon a time
ascents.comment: Everything in the valley is the same grade. vHard. Discovered some impromptu upward-press beta that felt so cool and controlled. Super punched to have thrown down this beautiful anti-style bounder without heinous desperation.

ascents.name: Leap of Faith
ascents.comment: Shirley loves this thing. The jump was OK, but the mantel was even better! PS: Shout out, that vB slab on the left face. Awesome knobs.

ascents.name: Unnamed Ahwanhee Lip Traverse
ascents.comment: Sweet consolation prize after flailing on Ahwahnee Arete. As far as lip traverses go, this was a pretty cool feature. Techy, tenuous first couple moves into more burly type slopers. Double toe hooks goes!

ascents.name: The Crack
ascents.comment: Not so bad. Just had to harness my inner Alan Haaaauser!

ascents.name: The Wave Right
ascents.comment: Up the right arete on the Wave boulder. Movement was actually alright. Just didn't feel much like pulling.

ascents.name: Franks Direct
ascents.comment: Hard first move and a freaking weird topout. But cool holds, I suppose. Right variation is better in my opinion.

ascents.name: Buck Rogers Right
ascents.comment: Mehhh.

ascents.name: Once upon a time
ascents.comment: Holy magical experience. Took 45 minutes to put our shoes on...and 5 more to send train. Shout out Jqee for snapping. Can you say Sandbox 2016 tank?

ascents.name: Obtuse
ascents.comment: Woah, this thing flows nicely. Big crimp face climbing, interesting movement, a bit exposed up top. This thing is ill.

ascents.name: Joe Cool
ascents.comment: Not quite as proud or as stiff as Fart Fig, but probably worth doing...as long as you don't waste any energy on this. You'll need it...for Fart Fig...

ascents.name: Bad Genes
ascents.comment: A tad better than Pimpin', in my opinion.

ascents.name: Ebonic Woman
ascents.comment: Did it twice. Start feels pretty awk. Campus beta was better. Neat feature, though. Who's Jane, again?

ascents.name: Double Decker
ascents.comment: Did it twice in a row. First was onsight, used a double kneebar. 4 star line. Second was Fanny's beta with like a super contrived press with left arm to get the foot up? Like what is that?

ascents.name: Left Brain
ascents.comment: Low start. Tricky first move. Didn't see the right start hold on flash go. Cool moves out of the roof and average sloper traverse once at the lip.

ascents.name: Slot Machine
ascents.comment: Starts at Tim's Sloper Problem and traverse to the top of Thighmaster. Some pretty good moves. Worth doing if  you're bored in the area and giving up on TSP.

ascents.name: Alien within
ascents.comment: Really dumb. Jaqueee's megaproj goes!

ascents.name: The Sickle
ascents.comment: Pretty darn dumb.

ascents.name: Roof Jugs Left
ascents.comment: So much fun, until I managed to turn the topout into a grovelly, thigh scraping, humpfest.

ascents.name: Roof Jugs Direct
ascents.comment: Direct and Left are both awesome. Very fun climbs! David's saddle mantle was classic.

ascents.name: Dirty
ascents.comment: They got the name right.

ascents.name: Dime Bag
ascents.comment: Pure as hell.

ascents.name: Maximum relaxum
ascents.comment: Felt dumb for trying to topout with the wrong holds 3 times before finding the jugs.

ascents.name: Crackhead
ascents.comment: Flashed this thing, but not without shedding some blood.

ascents.name: Speech Therapy
ascents.comment: If you're not double toe-hooking, you're doing it wrong.

ascents.name: Golden Eggs
ascents.comment: Sharp crimp. Neat drop knee beta. Dirty top.

ascents.name: Old and Serious
ascents.comment: Possibly my favorite climb of the trip. Set a problem in the gym with the same movement months before I'd ever seen this thing. Premonition?

ascents.name: 21st Century Digital Boy
ascents.comment: Sack, dude.

ascents.name: Kung Fu Grip
ascents.comment: Third go. Weird moves. Kinda cool.

ascents.name: The Drifter
ascents.comment: Short, but sweet double toe hook beta.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Direct version of The Spirit of the Forest. Funky landing hurt my ankle on first burn, be careful.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Left side on back of Greasefire boulder. Fun.

ascents.name: I aint broke, but I'm badly bent
ascents.comment: Kinda fun. First move wasn't terrible. Top was enjoyable.

ascents.name: Frank's Roof
ascents.comment: Great fun. Enjoyed this one a lot.

ascents.name: Safesurfer
ascents.comment: Fun big first move. Rest was meh.

ascents.name: All Nighter
ascents.comment: Did Weekender already. Not legit flash.

ascents.name: Brilliant Trees
ascents.comment: Didn't really like the movement.

ascents.name: Pirate Booty
ascents.comment: Foot slipped on flash go. Nooooo!

ascents.name: Beer Tumor
ascents.comment: Very fun. Loved it.

ascents.name: Rendezvous With An Alien
ascents.comment: Subtle, Chris.

ascents.name: New
ascents.comment: Start just to the right of Single Shot. Using good crimps and some stemming, make your way to the slopey topout. Good fun.

ascents.name: Yabo Roof
ascents.comment: Really fun. Big first move to really cool mantel.

ascents.name: The Pork Chop
ascents.comment: Very cool problem.

ascents.name: The Wave
ascents.comment: Seemed soft compared to the rest of Kraft. Fun though.

ascents.name: The Wave Direct
ascents.comment: Kinda fun. Not V3/4 like the book says, though. 10/26/15 Edit: Pyramid DG.

ascents.name: Visor Lip
ascents.comment: Decent movement. Top out was cool.

ascents.name: S is for Shame
ascents.comment: Meh. Good first move.

ascents.name: The Fang
ascents.comment: Fun moves.

ascents.name: The Warm Up
ascents.comment: Cool movement.

ascents.name: Apocalypse Now Stand
ascents.comment: Book says V3. Seemed a touch harder. Sweet line nonetheless.

ascents.name: Hueco Problem
ascents.comment: Just a tad soft. Awesome climb, though.

ascents.name: Dirt Bag
ascents.comment: Very soft. A couple of fun moves, though.

ascents.name: Railer
ascents.comment: Super fun roof to slab transition.

ascents.name: Samba
ascents.comment: Decent fun. Big move to the top.

ascents.name: Paul's Cock
ascents.comment: Dumb.

ascents.name: Trampass
ascents.comment: Kinda dumb.

ascents.name: White Flight
ascents.comment: One of my proudest sends. Great line.

ascents.name: Patina line
ascents.comment: Good beta makes the topout way more enjoyable.

ascents.name: Blade Runner
ascents.comment: Great problem. Awesome beta. 10/26/15 Edit: Pyramid DG.

ascents.name: Tri-Nitro-Toulumne
ascents.comment: Awesome line. Not close to 6C, though.

ascents.name: Pinky Piranha
ascents.comment: Couple of powerful moves.

ascents.name: King Tut
ascents.comment: Trust it!

ascents.name: Kodas Corner
ascents.comment: Classic.

ascents.name: Spiral Traverse
ascents.comment: Super fun.

ascents.name: Leaping Lizards
ascents.comment: 6C? No shot.

ascents.name: Baseball
ascents.comment: Really hard to figure out what's going on on this boulder as everything on Mountain Projjjy is refering to the pre-tilt era. I think we did something resembling what I believe this once was. Mostly.

ascents.name: Ghetto Simulator
ascents.comment: Woah, that's a lot of features. Good one to end the trip on!

ascents.name: Backdoor Man
ascents.comment: Yowza, this is amazing. The loose flakes up high are ok, until they're not ok...and you die.

ascents.name: Ostracizer
ascents.comment:
That juggy rail feature is un-rail sick. Topout was kinda weird, though.

Edit: Oh, the top has broken? Hueco is choss...

ascents.name: And the bucket of parts
ascents.comment: After four days of waiting for weather and park access, this was my first taste of Hueco choss. Not bad.

ascents.name: Nobody Gets Out of Here Alive
ascents.comment: It's basically Ghetto Simulator, but about a quarter of the moves with an easier finish. Let's give 'em the same grade!

ascents.name: Loss For Words
ascents.comment: All of the warmups here are insanely rad. Literally every hold is a giant feature. This was the best because it was like thrice as tall as the others.

ascents.name: Loss For Words
ascents.comment: All of the warmups here are insanely rad. Literally every hold is a giant feature. This was the best because it was like thrice as tall as the others.

ascents.name: Yep
ascents.comment: Shoutout Kian for grabbing her second v5 on the low start of this..with heinous beta no less.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: As if running all the way back to the car to get a left shoe wasn't warm-up enough, the traversy thing on the Meadow Boulder is. The last right hand lockoff pinch thing is so rad.

ascents.name: The Sleeping Lady
ascents.comment: We saved her for our sixth day on, just to make it a little more spicy. Luckily the Sleeping Lady is like a waitress at a Thai restaurant...noticed we were white, so she kept it mild. Shoutout Munchen Haus. They close early during the week, but if you can get there during their hours of operation, it's the best place in town.

ascents.name: The Classic
ascents.comment: Very cool lean-in perch move to match the ramp. They got the name right!

ascents.name: Madvillian
ascents.comment: Viktor used the college. Used its modern science to conduct strange, forbidden experiments.

ascents.name: The Scoop
ascents.comment: Get in there nice and deep-like, boy.

ascents.name: The Icicle
ascents.comment: Awfully fun for how small it is. Provides some much needed mantle practice.

ascents.name: Fun House Stairway
ascents.comment: No Stairway...denied!

ascents.name: Concavity
ascents.comment: Started every morning of the trip with a squat start. This one just happened to involve climbing.

ascents.name: Sunny and Steep
ascents.comment: Good holds, good movement, good size. I guess my one complaint is that it could be less soft? Shoutout Icicle Brewing: Roast Beef Au Jus was pretty good but small and unsatisfying after a day of climbing. Good beer though. Darker Persuasion german chocolate cake ale was deloyshous.

ascents.name: Natasha's Highball
ascents.comment: Lives up to the hype...in height, beauty, quality and softness!

ascents.name: Fire Pit
ascents.comment: David did not instill confidence on his chuff up this bad boy. Nor did Shirley being thrown off onto his ass. But pretty nice, directional holds all the way up. Good fun.

ascents.name: Spinal Snap Right Start
ascents.comment: I have a lot tee'd up at the Happies. Shout out the unreal double hack with Shirley and No-yes on this and adjacent boulders. That stall was what Iwo Jima.

ascents.name: Tombstone
ascents.comment: Sweet boulder and fun movement. Contrary to what you may have heard, the downclimb is not the crux. Shoutout Maria Onogirl for last-go softing this.

ascents.name: Shades of the Oldschool
ascents.comment: Sure, Spectre goes with one shoe, but this bad boy goes with three! This massive bounder is absolutely amazing. One of my proudest sends to date. 20 feet off the deck is not the time to be sussing beta. Unreal reachy, but you just have to believe. Thought I was going to have to bail and jump, but, in Whoville they say that Scooter's third arm grew three sizes that day.  Reaching that nipple felt better than any other move in recent memory. So scary and so rewarding. Stoked!
